1
00:00:41,159 --> 00:00:42,920
Who cares if it's one person or a few?

2
00:00:43,119 --> 00:00:44,960
Right now, the enemy is in the dark and we're in the open.

3
00:00:45,479 --> 00:00:46,520
If we really get into a fight,

4
00:00:46,520 --> 00:00:47,719
we'll be the ones at a disadvantage.

5
00:00:47,719 --> 00:00:49,079
Let's find a way to leave early.

6
00:00:49,399 --> 00:00:52,920
But where should we go?

7
00:00:53,439 --> 00:00:54,159
Yeah.

8
00:00:54,640 --> 00:00:55,799
All we know right now

9
00:00:55,799 --> 00:00:58,240
is that there's a secret passage between those two big toads.

10
00:00:58,640 --> 00:00:59,679
But in a place this big,

11
00:01:00,200 --> 00:01:01,920
where are we supposed to find those toads?

12
00:01:05,040 --> 00:01:06,280
Look, what's that up ahead?

13
00:01:13,519 --> 00:01:15,120
A patch of chicken-shit green.

14
00:01:15,120 --> 00:01:15,799
Get out of here.

15
00:01:16,680 --> 00:01:19,159
What Old Chen just said roughly means this:

16
00:01:19,480 --> 00:01:21,640
We've currently lost our way.

17
00:01:22,079 --> 00:01:23,640
It's like "not knowing the true face of Mount Lu,

18
00:01:23,640 --> 00:01:24,879
simply because we are in the mountain."

19
00:01:25,359 --> 00:01:26,879
We have to climb to the top of the mountain.

20
00:01:27,280 --> 00:01:28,599
"When you reach the summit,

21
00:01:28,840 --> 00:01:30,079
all other mountains look small."

22
00:01:30,560 --> 00:01:32,599
"The boundless scenery is at the perilous peak."

23
00:01:32,599 --> 00:01:34,599
To achieve our great goal.

24
00:01:35,079 --> 00:01:35,959
Is that what you meant?

25
00:01:36,079 --> 00:01:37,079
Lao Lu is right.

26
00:01:37,799 --> 00:01:38,959
That mountain up ahead

27
00:01:38,959 --> 00:01:40,480
is the highest one around here.

28
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:42,719
As long as we climb to the top

29
00:01:42,719 --> 00:01:43,760
at noon when the sun is brightest,

30
00:01:43,799 --> 00:01:45,840
we'll be able to see the terrain around here clearly.

31
00:01:46,079 --> 00:01:46,599
Right.

32
00:01:46,879 --> 00:01:49,239
By then, the fog should have cleared up too.

33
00:01:49,560 --> 00:01:51,239
Exactly. But the only problem is

34
00:01:51,239 --> 00:01:53,159
the fog clears up for too short a time.

35
00:01:53,159 --> 00:01:53,879
If we miss it,

36
00:01:53,879 --> 00:01:55,400
we'll have to stay another day.

37
00:01:55,560 --> 00:01:57,480
If someone is really ambushing us,

38
00:01:57,599 --> 00:01:58,879
we definitely can't stay any longer.

39
00:01:59,400 --> 00:02:02,560
We must reach the top before noon.

40
00:02:05,680 --> 00:02:06,280
Lao Lu,

41
00:02:06,959 --> 00:02:07,959
hurry up.

42
00:02:08,599 --> 00:02:10,560
You've been to so many places with us,

43
00:02:10,879 --> 00:02:12,479
how come you haven't improved at all?

44
00:02:12,680 --> 00:02:14,199
W-We have to be careful.

45
00:02:14,560 --> 00:02:16,000
Deep in the old forest,

46
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:17,639
what if a snake darts out?

47
00:02:17,639 --> 00:02:19,360
W-What do we do? What do we do?

48
00:02:25,520 --> 00:02:26,479
This huge cliff,

49
00:02:27,879 --> 00:02:29,879
e-even a gecko couldn't climb it.

50
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:33,240
Who said we have to climb up this cliff?

51
00:02:33,479 --> 00:02:34,680
Isn't this a cave?

52
00:02:35,400 --> 00:02:36,199
A cave?

53
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:37,599
Grab onto this, Lao Lu.

54
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:40,199
Take it easy.

55
00:02:42,599 --> 00:02:45,360
This vine is as thick as a person's forearm!

56
00:02:46,759 --> 00:02:48,759
What isn't thick and big in Nanyun?

57
00:02:56,199 --> 00:02:57,280
It's so huge.

58
00:03:00,439 --> 00:03:01,879
This isn't a natural cave.

59
00:03:02,840 --> 00:03:05,240
It was carved out by humans following the mountain's shape.

60
00:03:07,840 --> 00:03:09,879
This must be that big toad with its mouth open.

61
00:03:11,039 --> 00:03:13,039
What kind of dumb luck do we have?

62
00:03:13,400 --> 00:03:15,400
We just randomly picked a mountain to climb,

63
00:03:15,599 --> 00:03:16,840
and we stumbled upon the secret passage.

64
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:20,080
This is what they call finding it without any effort.

65
00:03:20,680 --> 00:03:21,599
Don't get excited just yet.

66
00:03:22,479 --> 00:03:23,560
The secret passage on the map

67
00:03:23,560 --> 00:03:25,159
is clearly in the valley.

68
00:03:25,479 --> 00:03:26,759
But this is halfway up the mountain.

69
00:03:26,879 --> 00:03:28,840
Are you going to dig a tunnel over there?

70
00:03:40,280 --> 00:03:41,360
Did a donkey kick you in the head?

71
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:43,400
Don't you think it looks like Contra?

72
00:03:43,400 --> 00:03:44,080
Get lost.

73
00:03:44,560 --> 00:03:45,800
The stone walls around here

74
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:47,479
are carved so roughly,

75
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:49,879
but the carvings on this stone door

76
00:03:50,080 --> 00:03:51,520
are so delicate.

77
00:03:53,280 --> 00:03:56,840
It doesn't seem to match the overall style.

78
00:04:15,280 --> 00:04:16,040
Let me tell you,

79
00:04:17,079 --> 00:04:18,639
I told you it was giants.

80
00:04:19,040 --> 00:04:21,199
They even need such a huge millstone just to grind soy milk.

81
00:04:23,240 --> 00:04:24,240
This is a winch.

82
00:04:24,519 --> 00:04:25,319
A winch?

83
00:04:27,800 --> 00:04:29,480
It should be used to pull open that stone door.

84
00:04:32,199 --> 00:04:33,079
Give me your rope.

85
00:04:34,120 --> 00:04:34,839
Hold this.

86
00:04:38,519 --> 00:04:39,120
Here.

87
00:04:57,959 --> 00:04:58,639
It's opening.

88
00:05:11,639 --> 00:05:13,079
This rope isn't tough enough.

89
00:05:15,120 --> 00:05:15,959
Then what do we do?

90
00:05:21,680 --> 00:05:23,839
Are you thinking of using a vine instead?

91
00:05:28,480 --> 00:05:31,040
This one won't work, right? It's too thin.

92
00:05:33,199 --> 00:05:34,480
Are there any more over here?

93
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:36,959
This one will do.

94
00:05:37,680 --> 00:05:39,639
Thick enough, and tough enough too.

95
00:05:45,720 --> 00:05:46,519
Commander Chen.

96
00:05:47,439 --> 00:05:49,560
You're not thinking of climbing up there, are you?

97
00:05:49,639 --> 00:05:51,000
How are we supposed to climb that?

98
00:05:51,240 --> 00:05:53,680
No one can be sure if this vine is stable.

99
00:05:54,399 --> 00:05:55,160
Then what should we do?

100
00:05:56,160 --> 00:05:57,439
This is the only way.

101
00:05:57,439 --> 00:05:58,800
I'll just have to go up and try.

102
00:06:02,040 --> 00:06:03,199
That's too dangerous.

103
00:06:03,199 --> 00:06:04,439
I can't let you go up there.

104
00:06:04,800 --> 00:06:06,079
You haven't even recovered from your fever yet.

105
00:06:28,360 --> 00:06:30,480
Don't worry, I'll be careful.

106
00:06:48,800 --> 00:06:50,279
Are you guys just going to let him do it?

107
00:06:50,680 --> 00:06:51,959
I won't care about his business anymore.

108
00:06:51,959 --> 00:06:52,800
No, no, this...

109
00:06:55,480 --> 00:06:56,600
If even you can't control him,

110
00:06:56,800 --> 00:06:58,079
don't count on us.

111
00:07:09,199 --> 00:07:11,879
Bro, that's enough.

112
00:07:18,759 --> 00:07:19,279
This...

113
00:07:46,360 --> 00:07:47,199
Be careful!

114
00:07:53,199 --> 00:07:53,800
Look at her.

115
00:07:54,199 --> 00:07:55,439
She just swore

116
00:07:55,439 --> 00:07:56,399
she wouldn't care anymore,

117
00:07:56,399 --> 00:07:57,480
and now she's telling him to be careful.

118
00:07:57,759 --> 00:07:58,959
That's just how Staff Officer He is.

119
00:08:26,639 --> 00:08:28,480
Good job, Old Chen!

120
00:08:35,039 --> 00:08:35,799
Chen Youxi!

121
00:08:50,159 --> 00:08:51,080
Hold on tight!

122
00:08:58,159 --> 00:08:58,600
This...

123
00:09:03,360 --> 00:09:05,200
Bro, are you okay?

124
00:09:06,200 --> 00:09:08,679
I'm fine. I just messed up the landing a bit.

125
00:09:09,039 --> 00:09:10,320
The process was still perfect.

126
00:09:13,320 --> 00:09:14,240
Get to work.

127
00:09:35,960 --> 00:09:37,639
When I went up just now,

128
00:09:37,639 --> 00:09:38,639
didn't I look super cool?

129
00:10:28,759 --> 00:10:29,799
I'm exhausted.

130
00:10:47,639 --> 00:10:48,840
It's really huge.

131
00:11:16,320 --> 00:11:17,080
Old Chen.

132
00:11:17,639 --> 00:11:18,919
Come here and see what this is.

133
00:11:25,559 --> 00:11:27,279
Anyway, running into this thing is bad luck.

134
00:11:27,279 --> 00:11:28,360
It's nothing good.

135
00:11:28,480 --> 00:11:29,639
Let's stay far away from it.

136
00:11:29,639 --> 00:11:30,960
Let's go. We'll walk around it.

137
00:11:31,360 --> 00:11:32,080
Let's go.

138
00:11:32,080 --> 00:11:32,679
Wait.

139
00:11:33,759 --> 00:11:35,360
Look at the arrangement of these stone figures.

140
00:11:35,360 --> 00:11:37,039
They're all based on feng shui principles.

141
00:11:37,840 --> 00:11:39,080
Nine above, one below.

142
00:11:39,639 --> 00:11:41,279
This is based on the Luoshu.

143
00:11:45,240 --> 00:11:46,159
It really is.

144
00:11:46,639 --> 00:11:49,320
It means this is an acupoint that changes feng shui.

145
00:11:49,600 --> 00:11:51,200
Digging a deep well inside the mountain belly.

146
00:11:51,559 --> 00:11:52,279
This exactly matches

147
00:11:52,279 --> 00:11:54,159
the Transformation Formula in the Classic of the Changing Dragon Veins.

148
00:11:54,519 --> 00:11:55,840
Changing the surroundings of the earth vein.

149
00:11:55,840 --> 00:11:58,039
The third of the nine acupoints.

150
00:11:58,480 --> 00:12:01,039
Fish act as dragon whiskers to gather gold and water.

151
00:12:01,480 --> 00:12:03,480
No, what does that mean?

152
00:12:04,120 --> 00:12:06,840
The Transformation Formula talks about methods to change feng shui.

153
00:12:06,919 --> 00:12:08,759
It's recorded in the Classic of the Changing Dragon Veins.

154
00:12:08,879 --> 00:12:11,519
To make this Dragon Vein change its shape and momentum,

155
00:12:11,679 --> 00:12:13,039
and alter the feng shui,

156
00:12:13,120 --> 00:12:15,440
you need to move at least

157
00:12:15,440 --> 00:12:17,320
nine important related acupoints around this earth vein.

158
00:12:17,320 --> 00:12:20,000
Could this be a coincidence?

159
00:12:20,320 --> 00:12:21,440
No, Lao Lu.

160
00:12:21,519 --> 00:12:23,279
Look at the stone slab in the middle.

161
00:12:23,519 --> 00:12:24,759
What's carved on it is exactly

162
00:12:24,759 --> 00:12:26,919
the third hexagram of the sixty-four hexagrams, Chun.

163
00:12:27,039 --> 00:12:27,840
The Chun hexagram.

164
00:12:28,080 --> 00:12:30,279
High mountains, deep wells, Luoshu arrangement.

165
00:12:30,399 --> 00:12:31,519
It matches perfectly.

166
00:12:31,919 --> 00:12:33,080
It is the third acupoint.

167
00:12:33,399 --> 00:12:35,039
Since the third acupoint is here,

168
00:12:35,600 --> 00:12:37,320
fish act as dragon whiskers to gather gold and water.

169
00:12:37,320 --> 00:12:39,679
Then there must be a ninth acupoint in this valley.

170
00:12:40,200 --> 00:12:41,879
Nine winding loops facing the mountain shore.

171
00:12:42,440 --> 00:12:43,120
Bro,

172
00:12:43,320 --> 00:12:44,720
what do these nine winding loops

173
00:12:44,720 --> 00:12:46,039
actually mean?

174
00:12:46,120 --> 00:12:46,919
Nine winding loops

175
00:12:46,919 --> 00:12:48,720
means that at the bend of the valley,

176
00:12:48,720 --> 00:12:50,720
a wooden mountain god temple must be built

177
00:12:50,879 --> 00:12:53,480
to add momentum to this water Dragon Vein,

178
00:12:53,480 --> 00:12:54,919
making the veins prominent.

179
00:12:55,320 --> 00:12:57,000
How do you know it's wooden?

180
00:12:57,399 --> 00:12:58,519
The ninth acupoint

181
00:12:58,879 --> 00:13:01,320
is the ninth hexagram, Xiaochu.

182
00:13:01,399 --> 00:13:03,200
The Xun palace in the Eight Trigrams belongs to wood.

183
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:05,759
I understand now.

184
00:13:05,919 --> 00:13:07,799
As long as we find the mountain god temple,

185
00:13:08,200 --> 00:13:10,639
we definitely won't be far from the King of Dian's tomb.

186
00:13:10,639 --> 00:13:11,320
Right?

187
00:13:11,679 --> 00:13:12,399
Exactly.

188
00:13:12,919 --> 00:13:13,840
Let's not waste any more time.

189
00:13:13,840 --> 00:13:14,480
Let's go quickly.

190
00:13:15,039 --> 00:13:15,600
Okay.

191
00:13:30,320 --> 00:13:31,519
Why is this door closed?

192
00:13:31,759 --> 00:13:32,120
This, this, this...

193
00:13:32,120 --> 00:13:34,200
This has cut off our retreat!

194
00:13:49,919 --> 00:13:50,799
What's that noise?

195
00:13:51,639 --> 00:13:52,440
What's that sound?

196
00:13:56,120 --> 00:13:57,120
What was that sound?

197
00:14:07,159 --> 00:14:08,840
Sharp-nosed viper.

198
00:14:09,840 --> 00:14:10,679
Speak English.

199
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:11,799
Sharp-nosed viper.

200
00:14:12,240 --> 00:14:13,399
It's a venomous snake.

201
00:14:13,799 --> 00:14:14,919
The venom of this snake

202
00:14:15,120 --> 00:14:16,759
is a hemotoxin made of proteins.

203
00:14:17,120 --> 00:14:18,600
It causes severe bleeding.

204
00:14:18,600 --> 00:14:19,519
Once bitten,

205
00:14:19,519 --> 00:14:21,320
the wound will keep bleeding

206
00:14:21,320 --> 00:14:22,279
and won't heal,

207
00:14:22,679 --> 00:14:23,919
leading to tissue necrosis.

208
00:14:24,120 --> 00:14:25,200
It's highly toxic.

209
00:14:25,320 --> 00:14:26,840
All that talk is useless.

210
00:14:26,840 --> 00:14:27,919
Tell me what to do!

211
00:14:28,480 --> 00:14:30,279
Snakes... snakes are afraid of...

212
00:14:30,639 --> 00:14:31,120
Smoke!

213
00:14:31,480 --> 00:14:32,120
Smoke!

214
00:14:33,720 --> 00:14:35,120
And pungent smells!

215
00:14:35,679 --> 00:14:36,720
Will essential balm work?

216
00:14:37,519 --> 00:14:39,200
Smell... here comes the smell!

217
00:14:39,200 --> 00:14:40,320
And loud noises!

218
00:14:40,320 --> 00:14:41,480
You should've said so earlier!

219
00:14:41,480 --> 00:14:42,200
I'll do it!

220
00:14:42,200 --> 00:14:43,480
Go, go, go!
